User Guide: Running the Batch Script for File Archiving
1. Create the Batch File
•	Save the code file with a .bat extension (e.g., move_files.bat) into the specified directory where the operation needs to perform.
2. Prepare the Target Directory (Optional)
•	Ensure a directory named Moved_data exists in the location where files will be moved.
•	If it does not exist, the script will automatically create it.
3. Execute the Script
•	Open Command Prompt.
•	Navigate to the directory where the batch file is saved using the cd command.
•	Run the batch file by typing its name and pressing Enter:
              move_files.bat
       OR
•	Simply double click on the script file.
4. Provide Input
•	When prompted, enter the number of months old the files should be to qualify for moving.
•	Press Enter to continue.
5. Monitor Progress
•	The script will display status messages during file movement and compression.
•	It may pause at certain points for your review before proceeding.
6. Verify Results
•	After completion, check the Moved_data directory.
•	Confirm that:
o	A subdirectory named with the year and month has been created.
o	Files have been moved and compressed into a ZIP file as expected.
